I dont think this logic belongs in a widget. I think the widget shuold call AbsenceRelationshipPersistenceService.canDelete() which contains this logic and passes back a Set&lt;Messages&gt; ,which is then checked by the widget.

In this way, the service layer has the business logic, not the widget. IMO it shuold be like this:

if (selectedAbsenceRelationship == null) {
   // Raise no selection message
} else if(!service.canDelete(selectedAbsenceRelationship).isEmpty()) {
   // Raise returned messages
} else {
   // Show popup
}

Tests are then much simpler in the widget, and the tests for business logic moves to service.
